<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How do I calculate electricity cost for an appliance?", answer: "Multiply the appliance wattage by hours of daily use to get watt-hours. Divide by 1,000 to get kilowatt-hours (kWh). Multiply by 30 for monthly kWh. Then multiply monthly kWh by your electricity rate (cost per kWh) to get the monthly cost. For example, a 100W light bulb used 8 hours per day: 100 x 8 / 1000 = 0.8 kWh/day x 30 = 24 kWh/month x $0.12 = $2.88/month." },
  { question: "What is the average electricity rate in the US?", answer: "The average residential electricity rate in the United States is approximately $0.12 to $0.16 per kWh, though rates vary significantly by state. Hawaii has the highest rates at over $0.30/kWh, while states like Louisiana and Washington have rates under $0.10/kWh. Check your utility bill for your exact rate." },
  { question: "Which appliances use the most electricity?", answer: "The biggest electricity consumers in a typical home are: central air conditioning (3,000-5,000W), electric water heaters (4,000-5,500W), clothes dryers (2,000-5,000W), electric ovens (2,000-5,000W), and space heaters (1,000-1,500W). Among always-on devices, refrigerators (100-400W) and entertainment systems contribute significantly over time." },
  { question: "How can I reduce my electricity bill?", answer: "Switch to LED bulbs (80% less energy than incandescent), use a programmable thermostat, unplug devices when not in use to eliminate standby power, run full loads in dishwashers and washing machines, air dry clothes when possible, and consider ENERGY STAR rated appliances when replacing old ones." },
  { question: "What is a kilowatt-hour (kWh)?", answer: "A kilowatt-hour is the amount of energy consumed by a 1,000-watt appliance running for one hour. It is the standard unit used by utility companies to measure and bill electricity consumption. A 100-watt light bulb running for 10 hours uses 1 kWh. Understanding kWh helps you compare the energy cost of different appliances." }
]) %>

<%= calculator_schema_with_ratings(
  name: "Electricity Usage Calculator",
  description: "Calculate electricity usage and monthly cost for multiple appliances based on wattage, daily usage hours, and your electricity rate.",
  url: everyday_electricity_usage_url,
  category: "UtilitiesApplication",
  calculator_slug: "electricity-usage"
) %>

